2026 Regular Session ENROLLED
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 192
BY SENATOR JACKSON-ANDREWS
A RESOLUTION
To urge and request members of the Louisiana Legislature to participate in a "ride along"
experience with the Department of Children and Family Services' child welfare
specialists.
WHEREAS, child welfare specialists dedicate their professional lives to protecting
children, strengthening families, and promoting the safety, permanency, and well-being of
vulnerable youth; and
WHEREAS, child welfare specialists serve on the front lines of child protection by
responding to reports of abuse and neglect, providing critical support services, advocating
for children's needs, and helping families access resources necessary for stability and
success; and
WHEREAS, the work performed by child welfare specialists requires compassion,
integrity, resilience, and sound professional judgment in often difficult and emotionally
demanding circumstances; and
WHEREAS, child welfare specialists collaborate with educators, healthcare
providers, law enforcement agencies, courts, and community organizations to ensure that
children and families receive comprehensive care and support; and
WHEREAS, the contributions of child welfare specialists play a vital role in
strengthening communities by promoting safe environments, reducing trauma, and helping
children achieve healthy and productive futures; and
WHEREAS, it is important to recognize and honor the dedication, sacrifice, and
commitment demonstrated daily by child welfare specialists across our communities; and
WHEREAS, being a child welfare specialist is highly demanding, in various
capacities such as child protection investigators, family services, or foster care workers; and
WHEREAS, the Legislature has demonstrated significant interest in protecting
Louisiana's children and the recurring concerns expressed by current and former child
welfare employees is of the utmost interest; and
