SR NO. 192 ENROLLED
WHEREAS, the best way to understand a person's situation and get a clear picture
of their daily experience is to "walk in their shoes"; and
WHEREAS, a "ride along" experience is an arranged opportunity, often used by law
enforcement and emergency services to allow a person to observe a professional doing their
job or performing a specific activity; and
WHEREAS, the members of the Legislature are in the unique position of not only
supporting child welfare specialists through legislation and through agency oversight, but
to truly understand all that the front-line workers do and see on any given day.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
does hereby urge and request members of the Louisiana Legislature to participate in a "ride
along" experience with the Department of Children and Family Services' child welfare
specialists.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Department of Children and Family Services
shall coordinate with legislators wishing to participate in a "ride along" experience to fully
understand what the child welfare specialist is responsible for at any given moment.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to each
member of the Louisiana Legislature via email transmission and to the secretary of the
Department of Children and Family Services.
PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE
